    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2013-03-06</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2013-04-12T19:24:04Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Amends the Commodity Exchange Act to revise the requirement that the Commodity Futures Trading Commission (CFTC), before promulgating a regulation or issuing an order, consider the costs and benefits of the action. Requires the CFTC, through the Office of the Chief Economist, to: (1) assess the costs and benefits, both qualitative and quantitative, of an intended regulation; and (2) propose or adopt a regulation only on a reasoned determination that the benefits justify the costs.</p> <p>Lists additional mandatory considerations for the CFTC to evaluate in making a reasoned determination of the costs and the benefits, including the impact on market liquidity in the futures and swaps markets, as well as alternatives to direct regulation.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>To improve consideration by the Commodity Futures Trading Commission of the costs and benefits of its regulations and orders.</title>
